            <head>Act 1.</head>
               <div type="scene" n="1">
               <head>Scene 1.</head>
                  <!--I used the <choice> tag with <orig> and <reg> for the long s.
                     It's crazy and messy and I'm not sure it's worth it, but at least
                     it's cool!-->
               <stage><hi rend="sc">Shatterbrain's</hi>Lodgings. A Dre<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>ss</reg>
                  </choice>ing-Table, with a 
               Gla<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>s, &amp;c. Frank a<choice>
                     <orig>&longs;</orig>
                     <reg>s</reg>
                     </choice>leep in a Chair. <hi rend="sc">Landlady</hi> 
               enters in a hurry.</stage>
               <sp who="#land"> 
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>Mr. Frank--Mr. Frank!</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>What's the matter?</p></sp>
               <sp who="#land">
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>Rou<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>e, rou<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>e, man!</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>Is my ma<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ter come home?</p></sp>
               <sp who="#land">
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>Your ma<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ter come home? no, he's not-
               but there's the Doctor below in his chariot, come to 
               carry him to his bride.</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>Yaw-have I <choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>lpt long?</p></sp>
               <sp who="#land">
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>You are a<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>leep <choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>till, one would think-I 
               tell you there is your ma<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ter's father-in-law that is to
               be, come to fetch him away!</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>My ma<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ter's father-in-law that is to be, 
               come to fetch him away!</p></sp>
               <sp who="#land">
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>Ay.</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>Well-what <choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>hall we do?</p></sp>
               <sp who="#land">
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>Nay, I don't know-I come to a<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>k you.</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>If I was not acquainted with my ma<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ter
               now, I <choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>hould naturally conclude that the had either
               hanged, or drown'd him<choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>elf in order to aviod being
               married.</p></sp>
               <sp who="#land">
                  <speaker>Land.</speaker>
                  <p>Oh, he's a <choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ad gentleman!</p></sp>
               <sp who="#frank">
                  <speaker>Frank.</speaker>
                  <p>He is a little out of the way <choice>
                  <orig>&longs;</orig>
                  <reg>s</reg>
                  </choice>ometimes, 
               indeed.</p></sp>
